1. DEFINITIONS

   "Software" means the Guarch Protocol Suite source code,
   documentation, binaries, and all associated files in this
   repository.

   "Derivative Work" means any software that incorporates,
   modifies, extends, or is substantially based on the
   Software's source code, architecture, protocol
   implementations, or cryptographic handshake sequences.

   "Sell" means to distribute the Software or a Derivative
   Work itself as a paid product, charging users for access
   to the software, its binaries, or its source code.

   "Ancillary Services" means services built around the
   Software that do not involve selling the Software itself,
   including but not limited to: selling server
   configurations, hosting proxy servers, providing managed
   VPN/proxy services, offering technical support, or
   distributing configuration files.


